{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and Percy hauls the last of the stuff out, exhausted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps back in and looks around, unable to believe there's no mouse cowering in the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the men approach, keeping straight faces, navigating the crap in the corridor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Gosh.
{DIALOGUE}: Ain't in there, huh?
{DIALOGUE}: Don't that beat the mousie band?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy keeps scanning the restraint room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others all look to Paul, waiting for him to speak--you're the boss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Percy.
{DIALOGUE}: You want to think about what you were doing just now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{META_DATA}: (turns, glaring)
{DIALOGUE}: I know what I was doing.
{DIALOGUE}: Trying to get the mouse.
{DIALOGUE}: You blind?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: You also scared the living crap out of me and Bill.
{DIALOGUE}: And them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He cocks a thumb at the inmates in their cells.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: So what?
{DIALOGUE}: They aren't in cradle- school, case you didn't notice...
{META_DATA}: (directed at Paul)
{DIALOGUE}: ...although you treat them that way half the time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: We don't scare 'em any more than we have to, Percy.
{DIALOGUE}: They're under enough strain as it is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Men under strain can snap.
{DIALOGUE}: Hurt themselves.
{DIALOGUE}: Hurt others.
{DIALOGUE}: That's why our job is talking, not yelling.
