{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SLOW TRACKING SHOT OF THE GREEN FLOOR takes us past a tiny scrap of break...and then another...and then past a mousetrap primed with a scrap of bacon...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and we keep following a long trail of bread scraps and mousetraps until we come to Percy, alone on the Mile, carefully laying the last mousetrap down...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and he scoots back against the desk to wait, crouched and holding his breath, eyes riveted to the restraint room door for any sign of his furry nemesis...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and CAMERA BOOMS SLOWLY DOWN off his face, dipping down to floor level...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...where the mouse is revealed under the desk, peering in the same direction as Percy, wondering what the hell's so interesting down there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It hops further out to see...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE OF PERCY FROM FLOOR LEVEL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and the mouse enters frame, hopping out a few more steps, mouse and man staring in the same direction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy turns, looks down at the mouse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse turns, looks up at Percy...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and all hell breaks loose again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They race the Mile as before, Percy hollering and stomping all the way, mousetraps snapping and flying up into frame as they go charging wildly past the cells.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse wins again.
