{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: What do I do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Watch and learn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul motions Percy behind the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy sighs, takes his spot next to Jack Van Hay, peers through the wire mesh as Toot plops into Old Sparky, wriggling his skinny ass to get comfy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOOT
{DIALOGUE}: Sittin' down, sittin' down, takin' a seat in Old Sparky's lap...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and Dean kneel to apply the ankle clamps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal steps in from the side, pressing down on the condemned man's left arm to keep him in place until the ankle clamps are secure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry moves in from the other side, securing the right arm clamp.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOOT
{DIALOGUE}: Gettin' clamped, gettin' clamped, gettin'--ow, shit, watch the skin!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul signals "ankles secure."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal holsters his pistol, applies the final clamp to the left arm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Roll on one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEHIND THE PARTITION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Van Hay mimes turning the generator knob up, whispering:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VAN HAY
{DIALOGUE}: "Roll on one" means I turn the generator up full.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll see the lights go brighter in half the prison...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME MAIN CHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as Brutal steps before the "condemned" and pronounces:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Arlen Bitterbuck, you have been condemned to die by a jury of your peers, sentence imposed by a judge in good standing in this state.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you have anything to say before the sentence is carried out?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOOT
{META_DATA}: (gleefully)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah!
{DIALOGUE}: I want a fried chicken dinner with gravy on the taters, I want to shit in your hat, and I got to have Mae West sit on my face, because I am one horny motherfucker!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal tries to hold on, but it's impossible--he cracks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everybody falls apart, howling helplessly with laughter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even Jack Van Hay is guffawing behind his partition.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Only Paul is reining it in--he's a little too pissed to go with it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He waits until the laughing fit starts to pass, then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Shut up, Brutal.
{DIALOGUE}: That goes for everybody.
{DIALOGUE}: I want quiet in here.
{META_DATA}: (turns)
{DIALOGUE}: Toot, another remark like that, I'll have Van Hay roll on two for real.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{META_DATA}: (beat, gently)
{DIALOGUE}: It was pretty funny.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: That's why I don't like it.
{DIALOGUE}: Tomorrow night we're doing this for real.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want somebody remembering a stupid joke like that and getting going again.
{META_DATA}: (off their looks)
{DIALOGUE}: Ever try not laughing in church once something funny gets stuck in your head.
{DIALOGUE}: Same goddamn thing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry, Paul.
{DIALOGUE}: You're right.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's keep going.
{DIALOGUE}: Harry...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry takes a black mask and snugs it down over Toot's head, leaving only the crown of his head exposed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal takes a large sponge, dips it in a steel bucket, mimes soaking it...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEHIND THE PARTITION
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: What's with the sponge?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VAN HAY
{DIALOGUE}: You soak it in brine, get it good and wet.
{DIALOGUE}: Conducts the electricity directly to the brain, fast like a bullet.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't ever want to throw the switch on a man without that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME MAIN CHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as the sponge is placed atop Toot's head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry now lowers the steel cap and Brutal secures the straps.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Arlen Bitterbuck, electricity shall now be passed through your body until you are dead, in accordance with the state law.
{DIALOGUE}: God have mercy on your soul.
{META_DATA}: (to Van Hay)
{DIALOGUE}: Roll on two.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEHIND THE PARTITION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Van Hay mimes flipping the switch, looks to Percy:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VAN HAY
{DIALOGUE}: And that's that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME MAIN CHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toot can't resist--he starts bucking and flailing:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TOOT
{DIALOGUE}: Now I'm fryin'!
{DIALOGUE}: Fryin'!
{DIALOGUE}: Geeaaah!
{DIALOGUE}: Fryin' like a done tom turkey!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul rolls his eyes at Brutal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal shifts his gaze past him and nods--look behind you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: One of the witnesses showed up a day early.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sitting on the door sill, watching them with beady eyes, is the mouse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul turns back, addresses the room:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: All right, let's go again and do it right this time!
{DIALOGUE}: Get that idiot out of the chair...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH WIDE ANGLE OF EXECUTION CHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal and Harry start undoing Toot's clamps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everybody relaxes, drifting from their positions...
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAME ANGLE AS ABOVE - NEXT NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and the room is now quietly filling up with WITNESSES trickling in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People speak in whispers, if at all.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BITTERBUCK'S CELL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck, the top of his head now shaved, is speaking quietly as Paul listens:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BITTERBUCK
{DIALOGUE}: You think if a man sincerely repents on what he done wrong, he might get to go back to the time that was happiest for him and live there forever?
{DIALOGUE}: Could that be what heaven is like?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul doesn't think so--but that's not what Bitterbuck needs to hear, so the lie comes easy:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I just about believe that very thing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BITTERBUCK
{DIALOGUE}: Had me a young wife when I was eighteen.
{DIALOGUE}: Spent our first summer in the mountains.
{DIALOGUE}: Made love every night.
{DIALOGUE}: She'd just lie there after, bare-breasted in the firelight, and we'd talk sometimes till the sun come up.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: That was my best time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal appears at the door, checks his pocketwatch, nods to Paul.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck takes a deep breath, getting himself ready.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: It'll be fine.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll do fine.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. EXECUTION CHAMBER - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE SPONGE is pulled sopping wet from the bucket of brine, dripping a trail of water across the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal places it atop Bitterbuck's head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Water courses down the sides of the condemned man's mask and neck, pooling on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cap is lowered, the straps secured.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All we hear now is the sound of Bitterbuck's BREATHING growing louder and faster under the mask...until, softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Roll on two.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The switch is thrown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck surges forward against the straps, riding the powerful current.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some witnesses turn away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and Brutal maintain grim eye contact with each other, waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind the partition, Percy watches through the mesh with gleaming eyes, wishing he could see better.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Van Hay kills the current.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck goes limp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A DOCTOR steps forward, checks for a heartbeat, shakes his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The switch is thrown a second time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck surges forward again, riding the current all the way...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK ACCESS TUNNEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bitterbuck's dead face stares up at us from a gurney.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A hand reaches down, gives his cheek a squeeze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TILT UP to:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Adios, Chief.
{DIALOGUE}: Drop us a card from hell, let us know if it's hot enough.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal knocks Percy's hand away, shoves him aside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: He's paid what he's owed.
{DIALOGUE}: He's square with the house again, so keep your goddamn hands off him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He draws the sheet over Bitterbuck's face, wheels the gurney down the tunnel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy throws a look to Paul.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: What's up his ass?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: You, Percy.
{DIALOGUE}: Always you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul brushes past him, but:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: You gotta hate the new boy?
{DIALOGUE}: That the way it is around here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{META_DATA}: (turns back)
{DIALOGUE}: Why not just move on?
{DIALOGUE}: Go to Briar Ridge.
{META_DATA}: (off his look)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I know about it.
{DIALOGUE}: Sounds like a good job.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: I might take it, too.
{DIALOGUE}: Soon as you put me out front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul cocks his head--excuse me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: You heard me.
{DIALOGUE}: I want Brutal's spot for the next execution.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: What's with you?
{DIALOGUE}: Seeing a man die isn't enough?
{DIALOGUE}: You gotta be close enough to smell his nuts cook?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: I wanna be out front, is all.
{DIALOGUE}: Just one time.
{DIALOGUE}: Then you'll be rid of me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: If I say no?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: I might just stick around for good, make me a career of this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul just shakes his head in wonder and walks away.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COFFEY'S CELL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's lying on his bunk, weeping quiet tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stirs at the sound of GIGGLING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits up, peers curiously through the bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Del?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE GUARD STATION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul glances up from writing in the daily log.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes back to writing--and the GIGGLING comes again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Delacroix?
{DIALOGUE}: That you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just more giggling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul rises, walks down the Mile to Delacroix's cell--and stops, staring in through the bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PAUL'S INNER OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal and Dean are having lunch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul pokes his head in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: You are not gonna believe this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME E BLOCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men follow Paul onto the Mile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: By now, Del is CACKLING WILDLY in his cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal shoots Paul a look--has he gone insane?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul gestures "see for yourself."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They arrive at the bars...and find the mouse sitting on Del's shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del looks up, giggling like a kid at Christmas.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Look!
{DIALOGUE}: I done tame me dat mouse!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: We see that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Watch dis!
{DIALOGUE}: Watch what he do!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stretches out his left arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse crawls over the top of his head, scampers along his arm to the wrist, turns around and scampers back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guards just stand there, staring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Ain't he sumpthin now?
{DIALOGUE}: Ain't Mr. Jingles smart?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Jingles?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Dat his name.
{DIALOGUE}: He whisper it in my ear.
{DIALOGUE}: Cap'n, can I have a box for my mouse so he can sleep in here wi' me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I notice your English gets better when you want something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Wanna see what else he can do?
{DIALOGUE}: Watch, watch, watch...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts the mouse on the floor, grabs a small wooden spool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse sees it, poises like a man getting ready for a race.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: We play fetch, Mr. Jingles?
{DIALOGUE}: We play fetch?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tosses the spool across the floor, bounces it against the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse goes after it like a dog after a stick--and proceeds to push it back to the bunk, rolling it with its front paws all the way to Delacroix's feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: By now, the guard's jaws are hanging open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul's got a funny little chill running up his spine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: He fetch it ever' time.
{DIALOGUE}: Smart as hell, ain't he?
{DIALOGUE}: We do da trick again, watch, watch, watch...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Again he throws the spool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Again the mouse goes after it, starts rolling it back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del howls with laughter, claps his hands like a kid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal murmurs to the others:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Who's training who here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: That's some smart mouse, Del.
{DIALOGUE}: Like he's a circus mouse or something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: A circus mouse!
{DIALOGUE}: Dat jus' what he is, too!
{DIALOGUE}: A circus mouse!
{DIALOGUE}: I get outta here, he make me rich, see if he don't!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up the spool again, makes a drumroll sound, tosses it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse does its thing, rolling the spool back...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...as Percy enters the scene.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del catches sight of him and scoops up his mouse, drawing fearfully back on his bunk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries to hide Mr. Jingles in his hands--but the mouse wriggles from his grasp and scampers up on top of his head, where he regards Percy with mistrustful, beady mouse eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Well, well.
{DIALOGUE}: Looks like you found yourself a new friend, Eddie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del tries to offer some defiance--but all he can manage is:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Don' hurt him, 'kay?
{DIALOGUE}: 'kay?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy shrugs as if to say "no skin off me", looks to Paul.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: That the one I chased?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{META_DATA}: (level)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, that's the one.
{DIALOGUE}: Only Del says his name is Mr. Jingles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Is that so?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul trades a look with the others, everybody wondering just what the hell's going through Percy's mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Del was just asking for a box.
{DIALOGUE}: He thinks the mouse will sleep in it, I guess.
{DIALOGUE}: That he might keep it for a pet.
{DIALOGUE}: What do you think?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: I think it'll shit up his nose some night and run away, but I guess that's Del's lookout.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: We oughtta find a cigar box.
{DIALOGUE}: Get some cotton batting from he dispensary to line it with.
{DIALOGUE}: That should do real nice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy walks away, leaving them dumbstruck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul turns to the others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Of all the things they've seen in the last few minutes, Percy being nice is the most amazing of all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Man said get a cigar box.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRISON ADMINISTRATION BUILDING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul comes up the stairs to the warden's office...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WARDEN MOORES' OFFICE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and enters to find Hal staring out the window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Hal?
{DIALOGUE}: You wanted to see me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Paul.
{DIALOGUE}: Close the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal's speech is halting, his thoughts disjointed and slow:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Uh.
{DIALOGUE}: So you know.
{DIALOGUE}: You got a new prisoner coming in tomorrow.
{DIALOGUE}: William Wharton.
{DIALOGUE}: Young kid.
{DIALOGUE}: Wild as hell, judging from this...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up the report, trying to focus his thoughts:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: ...been rambling all over the state last few years, causing all kinds of trouble.
{DIALOGUE}: Finally hit big time.
{DIALOGUE}: Killed three people in a holdup, including a pregnant woman.
{DIALOGUE}: Got "Billy the Kid" tattooed on his left arm...bad news all around...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He trails off, no longer able to focus on the words.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is shocked to see tears spill silently down his cheeks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Hal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: It's a tumor, Paul.
{DIALOGUE}: A brain tumor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul doesn't know what to say.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal looks at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: They got X-ray pictures of it.
{DIALOGUE}: It's the size of a lemon, they said, and way down deep inside where they can't operate.
{DIALOGUE}: They say she'll be dead by Christmas.
{DIALOGUE}: I haven't told her.
{DIALOGUE}: I can't think how.
{DIALOGUE}: For the life of me, Paul, I can't think how to tell my wife she's going to die.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal Moores, one of the toughest and steadiest men you'd ever meets, starts to cry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He dissolves into great big gasping sobs, losing all control.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PAUL'S BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul lies awake, watching Jan sleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks troubled--not to mention feverish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It occurs to him how badly he has to pee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits up, clutching at a queasy stab of pain in his groin...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIVING ROOM STAIRS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and comes hurrying down the steps, clutching himself...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and he's moving even faster as he exits the kitchen, racing for the outhouse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He realizes he's not going to make it, stops to piss near the woodpile at the corner of the house...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and as he does, he's hit with the most stunning pain of his life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He buckles to his knees--it's only his flailing hand against the woodpile that prevents him from going face- first into his own piss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He crams his other hand to his mouth in an enormous effort not to scream and wake his wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He manages to ride it out until his bladder empties.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He falls onto his side, rolls over on the grass, and stares up at the sky with both hands pressed to his groin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: ...oh God...oh God...
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN BLACKNESS, A TITLE CARD APPEARS:
{META_DATA}: "Coffey's Hands"
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PAUL'S KITCHEN - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul looks feverish and clammy as he buttons up his uniform jacket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan is packing his lunch, throwing him looks, knowing how sick he is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: To the doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going.
{META_DATA}: (off her look)
{DIALOGUE}: Today.
{DIALOGUE}: Just as soon as we get the new inmate squares away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: That bad?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Oh yeah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hands him his brown-bagged lunch, kisses his face.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BRIAR RIDGE MENTAL HOSPITAL - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see a tattoo: "Billy the Kid."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TILT UP to WILLIAM WHARTON staring out the window, wearing a hospital gown, his face utterly blank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks heavily medicated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry, Dean, and Percy enter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy doesn't react, just keeps staring out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry waves his fingers in Billy's face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: Boy's doped to the gills.
{DIALOGUE}: Dean, hand me them clothes...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean relays some folded prison clothes to Harry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: William Wharton!
{DIALOGUE}: Hey!
{DIALOGUE}: I'm talking to you!
{DIALOGUE}: Put these clothes on!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy turns with a vacant look, takes the clothes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He fumbles with the shirt, drops the pants.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry and Dean sigh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They strip Billy's hospital gown off and proceed to put the shirt on him, guiding his limp arms through the sleeves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Hellraiser, huh?
{DIALOGUE}: Looks more like a limp noodle to me.
{DIALOGUE}: Hey!
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, you!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy looks up, meets Percy's eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: You been declared competent!
{DIALOGUE}: Know what that means?
{DIALOGUE}: Mean's you're gonna ride the lightning, son!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy does a quick impression of a man jittering and jerking in the electric chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Bzzzzzzzzt-zap!
{DIALOGUE}: Just like that!
{DIALOGUE}: How's it feel to know you're gonna die with your knees bent?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: C'mon, Percy, give us a hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Laughing, Percy picks up the pants.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They proceed to help Billy into them one leg at a time...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK TOILET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is trying to piss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Except for a few drops hitting the bowl, excruciating pain seems to be the only result.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gives up, grabs a towel, wipes the sweat from his feverish face...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and steps gingerly from the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del's watching.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Don' look so good, boss.
{DIALOGUE}: Look like you runnin' you a fever.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul shoots him a baleful look--no kidding.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another voice calls softly from further down the Mile:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Boss Edgecomb?
{DIALOGUE}: Needs ta see you down here, boss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Got things to tend to just now, John Coffey.
{DIALOGUE}: You be still in your cell now, y'hear?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey falls silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul goes to the entrance door and peers through the viewing slot, anxious to have this over with...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COLD MOUNTAIN PENITENTIARY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The prison truck appears, swaying along the rutted road...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE TRUCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...while Billy Wharton stares at nothing, drool dripping from his slack mouth in long strings.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul watches the truck pull in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He draws away from the slot, proceeds toward the empty cell which used to be Bitterbuck's...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON TRUCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rear doors are swung open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry emerges.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean and Percy are guiding Billy by the arm, helping him down...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSIDE E BLOCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul waits at the empty cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE PANS TIGHT to Coffey at his bars, eyes widening in a blossoming of some nameless fear or dread.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something bad's coming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A whisper:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Careful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OUTSIDE E BLOCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy is brought to the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean pulls his keys, starts to unlock it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We PUSH IN on Billy's face, where the tiniest trace of a smile is starting to grow...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSIDE E BLOCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and Coffey's unease grows with it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: he presses his face to the bars, his whispering becoming more urgent:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Careful.
{DIALOGUE}: Careful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul hears him, glances back with a puzzled look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's gaze is directed at the door, which is being unlocked...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE DOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and opened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In that moment, the slack look on Billy's face gives way to a wild grin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CRAZED SCREECH leaps from his throat, a cross between a rebel yell and a dog being tortured, freezing everybody's blood in their veins--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Yeeeeeeehaaaawwwwwwrooooo!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: --and he drops his wrist-chain down over Dean's head, jerks it tight, begins to strangle him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean lurches forward, Billy riding/propelling him through the door onto the Mile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy stands frozen in the doorway, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry shoves him aside and jumps on Billy from behind, trying to get him off Dean.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean is choking, turning purple.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul rushes from the cell to join the fray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy whirls, delivering a stunning kick to Paul's groin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul's bladder pain goes nuclear--he falls back in agony, clutching himself and sucking air through his teeth, unable even to scream.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy rams an elbow into Harry's face, knocks him sprawling on the desk, screaming and laughing and howling all the while:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: WHOOOEE, BOYS!
{DIALOGUE}: AIN'T THIS A PARTY, NOW?
{DIALOGUE}: IS IT, OR WHAT?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul forces himself to his feet, pulls his revolver, draws down on Billy...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: LET HIM GO!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...but Billy jerks Dean around, using him as a shield...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: G'WAN, SHOOT!
{DIALOGUE}: SEE WHO YA HIT!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean is choking, dying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is shifting his aim, trying for a clear shot, not getting one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy's still just inside the doorway, pressed against the wall with fear...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: HIT HIM, PERCY!
{DIALOGUE}: GODDAMN IT, HIT HIM!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: C'MON, PERCY, HIT ME!
{DIALOGUE}: HIT ME, YOU LIMP NOODLE, HIT ME!
{DIALOGUE}: YEEHAWWW!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and suddenly a hand comes in, grabs the hickory stick out of Percy's grasp, raises it high--
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: --it's Brutal coming through the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He swings the baton and lands an awesome blow to Billy's head--THUMP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The force of it spins Billy off his feet and slams him flat on his back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean crawls away, gulping ragged breaths of air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Amazingly, Billy's still conscious--he looks up at Brutal and laughs:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Big fucker.
{DIALOGUE}: Snuck up on me.
{DIALOGUE}: No fair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still laughing, he makes another grab at Dean.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal whacks him again, turning his lights out for good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal drops to Dean's side, helping him hack air back into his lungs:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Breathe...breathe...that's it...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everybody's reining in their adrenaline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul glares at Harry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: We thought he was doped.
{META_DATA}: (to Percy)
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't we?
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't we all of us think he was doped?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy nods, still numb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is furious:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't ask?
{DIALOGUE}: I guess that's not a mistake you'll be need to make again anytime soon, is it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry shakes his head miserably.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul grabs Billy by the feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Grab his arms!
{DIALOGUE}: You too, Percy!
{META_DATA}: (off Percy's hesitation)
{DIALOGUE}: Percy, goddamn it, get your feet out of cement and help us out here!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy finally unfreezes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The three of them hoist Billy up in a dead-lift, get him in his cell, toss him on the cot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They step out, slam the door, lock it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul looks to Harry and Brutal.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Get Dean looked at right away, make sure he's all right.
{DIALOGUE}: Percy, you go make a report to the warden for me.
{DIALOGUE}: Start off by saying the situation is under control-- it's not a story, he won't appreciate you drawing out the suspense.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: What about you?
{DIALOGUE}: You look about ready to collapse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I've got the Mile till you all get back.
{DIALOGUE}: Go on now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They all exit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As soon as he's alone, Paul gives in to the pain, holding his crotch and sinking to his knees with a moan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's so bad he actually lays down on the Mile, face pressed against the cool linoleum, wishing he were dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A stretch of silence...and then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Boss?
{DIALOGUE}: Needs ta see ya down here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: This is not a good time, John Coffey.
{DIALOGUE}: Not a good time at all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: But I needs ta see ya, boss.
{DIALOGUE}: I needs ta talk t'ya.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul sighs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Things couldn't get much worse than this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rises with a supreme effort, walks painfully down the Mile...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COFFEY'S CELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and finds Coffey waiting at his bars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Closer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm alone here right now, John.
{DIALOGUE}: Figure this is close enough.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Boss, please.
{DIALOGUE}: I got to whisper in your ear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul blinks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maybe it's the fever clouding his brain, or maybe...hell, is this what being hypnotized is like?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries to shake the sensation off, comes a little closer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Boss?
{DIALOGUE}: You know you not s'pose to do dat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Mind your business, Del.
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want, John Coffey?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Just to help.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hand shoots out, grabs Paul by the collar, jerks him close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul makes a panic-grab for his revolver...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...but Coffey lays his free hand atop Paul's, eases his grip from the gun--no need for that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's hand then drifts slowly down, easing to Paul's crotch...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{META_DATA}: (stunned, frozen)
{DIALOGUE}: What are you...doing?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and something goes WHUMP through Paul's body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He arches back with his mouth agape and arms outstretched as a rush of energy seems to pass from Paul through Coffey's hand...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and then it's over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul comes back to the real world, weak against the bars, realizes Del is hollering in his cell:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: HELP!
{DIALOGUE}: JOHN COFFEY'S KILLING BOSS EDGECOMB!
{DIALOGUE}: HELP!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Del, Chrissake, settle down, I'm fine...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It dawns on him that he really is fine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fever's gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: So is the pain in his groin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John Coffey, though, seems to be having trouble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits down on his bunk, bends forward, gagging like a man with a chicken bone caught in his throat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: John?
{DIALOGUE}: John, what's wrong?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul fumbles his keys to the lock, unsure if he should open the door, watching the big man's contortions grow stronger like a cat trying to cough up a hairball...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and then comes an unpleasant, gagging/retching sound as Coffey's lips draw back from his teeth in a kind of godawful sneer...and he exhales a cloud of what look like tiny black insects.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They swirl furiously in front of his face, turn white...and disappear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul just stares, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: What did you do, big boy?
{DIALOGUE}: What did you do to me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: I helped it.
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't I help it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, but...how?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey shrugs--it's something that just is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Just took it back, is all.
{DIALOGUE}: Awful tired now, boss.
{DIALOGUE}: Dog tired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls onto his bunk, faces the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul just stares at him, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and walks up the Mile, his stiffness and pain now gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del watches him go by, also stunned:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: What dat man do to you?
{DIALOGUE}: He throw some gris-gris on you?
{META_DATA}: (off Paul's look)
{DIALOGUE}: You look diff'int!
{DIALOGUE}: Even walk diff'int.
{DIALOGUE}: Like y'all better!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: You're imagining thing.
{DIALOGUE}: Lie down, Del.
{DIALOGUE}: Get you some rest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul continues up the Mile...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E BLOCK TOILET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and steps back into the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not trusting this situation for even a moment, Paul opens his fly, takes a deep breath to prepare himself for the pain, starts to pee...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and we hear a healthy stream of water hitting the bowl.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The look on Paul's face says it all--blessed relief.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PAUL'S HOUSE - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul comes home from work, still looking numb about the whole thing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drifts to the kitchen door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan's at the counter, slicing vegetables for dinner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glances at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, honey.
{DIALOGUE}: How are you feeling?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Um...not too bad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul's eyes drift down to admire her ass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: What did the doctor say?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No response.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's too busy staring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns again--he glances hastily up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, you know doctors.
{DIALOGUE}: Gobble-de- gook mostly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns back, keeps working.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He crosses the room, eyeing her ass all the way...and surprised her by pressing up against her from behind, running his hands along her hips.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Paul?
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts laying kisses on the back of her neck, giving her pleasant shivers, murmuring:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: What's it feel like?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: I know what it feels like...it feels great...but...Paul...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's getting her breathless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns into his arms and they get into some passionate kissing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's not too long before they're frantically peeling each other's clothes off...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and we find them having a wild tumble in the sheets, both moaning and groaning, sweating and panting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pushes him flat on the bed, pauses to catch her breath...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Those must've been some pills.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and they keep going, rutting like crazed weasels...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...as their moans go drifting into the night...
{META_DATA}: FADE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SAME ANGLE AS ABOVE - DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and they're still moaning up there as the sun creeps up.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan falls back, exhausted after the latest go-round.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She catches her breath, looks over at Paul, and finally:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Paul?
{DIALOGUE}: Not that I'm complaining.
{DIALOGUE}: But we haven't gone four times in one night since we were nineteen.
{META_DATA}: (off his look)
{DIALOGUE}: You wanna tell me just what the hell's going on?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Well...thing is...I never actually got to the doctor yesterday...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She gives him a look--oh?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LIVING ROOM - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is on the phone:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Brutal?
{DIALOGUE}: Listen...I'm thinking of taking the morning off sick.
{DIALOGUE}: You cover the fort for me?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: That's swell.
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I'm sure I'll feel better.
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hangs up, turns to Jan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: You sure you ought to do this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not sure what I'm sure of.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ROAD TO TEFTON - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul's model T comes putt-putting up the road past a sign: "Trapingus County Welcomes You."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOUSE IN TEFTON - BACK PORCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BURT HAMMERSMITH, public defender for Trapingus County, sits with a cold soda and a magazine, watching his TWO CHILDREN playing on a swing at the far end of the backyard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The screen door opens and CYNTHIA HAMMERSMITH ushers Paul out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYNTHIA
{DIALOGUE}: I offer you a cold drink?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, ma'am, a cold drink would be fine.
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She goes back inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt rises.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Hammersmith.
{DIALOGUE}: Your office said I'd find you at home today.
{DIALOGUE}: I hope I'm not troubling you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: That depends, Mr.--?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Paul Edgecomb.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm the E Block superintendant at Cold Mountain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: The Green Mile.
{DIALOGUE}: I've heard of it.
{DIALOGUE}: Lost a few clients your way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: That's why I'm here.
{DIALOGUE}: I'd like to ask you about one of them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt settles back down, motions "please sit".
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Which client?
{DIALOGUE}: Now you got my curiosity aroused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: John Coffey.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Ah, Coffey.
{DIALOGUE}: He causing you problems?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No, can't say he is.
{DIALOGUE}: He doesn't like the dark.
{DIALOGUE}: He cries on occasion.
{DIALOGUE}: Other than that...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Cries, does he?
{DIALOGUE}: Well, he's got a lot to cry about, I'd say.
{DIALOGUE}: You know what he did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{META_DATA}: (nods)
{DIALOGUE}: I read the court transcripts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cynthia reappears, hands Paul a cold root beer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, Missus.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYNTHIA
{DIALOGUE}: My pleasure.
{DIALOGUE}: Kids!
{DIALOGUE}: Lunch is about ready!
{DIALOGUE}: Y'all come on up!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She goes back inside, but the kids aren't quite able to tear themselves away from their play.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: What exactly are you trying to find out?
{DIALOGUE}: Satisfy my curiosity, I'll see if I can satisfy yours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I've wondered if he ever did anything like that before.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{DIALOGUE}: Has he said anything?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: But a man who does a thing like that has often developed a taste for it over time.
{DIALOGUE}: Occurred to me it might be easy enough to follow his backtrail and find out.
{DIALOGUE}: A man his size, and colored to boot, can't be that hard to trace.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.
{DIALOGUE}: Believe me, we tried.
{DIALOGUE}: It's like he dropped out of the sky.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: How do you explain that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: We're in a Depression.
{DIALOGUE}: A third of the country's out of work.
{DIALOGUE}: People are drifting by the thousands, looking for work, looking for that greener grass.
{DIALOGUE}: Even a giant like Coffey wouldn't get noticed everywhere he goes... not until he kills a couple of little girls.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: He's...strange, I admit.
{DIALOGUE}: But there doesn't seem to be any real violence in him.
{DIALOGUE}: I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.
{DIALOGUE}: I deal with 'em day in and day out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt smiles, realizing:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't come up here to ask me whether he might have killed before.
{DIALOGUE}: You came up here to see if I think he did it at all.
{DIALOGUE}: That's it, isn't it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Do you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.
{DIALOGUE}: He was found with the victims in his arms.
{DIALOGUE}: Blurted out a confession right then and there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Yet you defended him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Everyone is entitled to a defense.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cynthia hollers from an open window:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYNTHIA
{DIALOGUE}: Kids!
{DIALOGUE}: Lunch!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Y'all listen to your Momma, now!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kids start this way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt turns back to Paul.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Tell you something.
{DIALOGUE}: You listen close, too, because it might be something you need to know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm listening.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: We had us a dog.
{DIALOGUE}: No particular breed, but gentle.
{DIALOGUE}: Ready to lick your hand or fetch a stick.
{DIALOGUE}: Just a sweet mongrel, you know the kind.
{META_DATA}: (Paul nods)
{DIALOGUE}: In many way, a good mongrel dog is like you negro.
{DIALOGUE}: You get to know it, and often you get to love it.
{DIALOGUE}: It is of no particular use, but you keep it around because you think it loves you.
{DIALOGUE}: If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you never have to find out any different.
{DIALOGUE}: My wife and I were not so lucky.
{DIALOGUE}: Caleb.
{DIALOGUE}: Come here for a second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The little boy comes to him, staring at his feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt tires to raise the boy's chin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy resists for a moment...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: Please, son.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and then his face comes around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's horribly scarred on that side, the eye missing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: He has the one eye.
{DIALOGUE}: I suppose he's lucky not to be blind.
{DIALOGUE}: We get down on our knees and thank God for that much at least.
{DIALOGUE}: Right Caleb?
{META_DATA}: (the boy nods shyly)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, go on in now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy races inside after his sister.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul follows Burt's gaze off toward the rear of the property, where an unoccupied doghouse stands weathered and sad in the weeds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: That dog attacked my boy for no reason.
{DIALOGUE}: Just got it into his mind one day.
{DIALOGUE}: Same with John Coffey.
{DIALOGUE}: He was sorry afterwards, of that I have no doubt...but those little girls stayed raped and murdered nonetheless.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe he's never done it before--my dog never bit before, but I didn't concern myself with that.
{DIALOGUE}: I went out there with my rifle and grabbed his collar and blew his brains out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry for your trouble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt acknowledges the condolence with a gracious nod.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm as enlightened as the next man, Mr. Edgecomb.
{DIALOGUE}: I would not bring back slavery for all the tea in China.
{DIALOGUE}: I believe we have to be humane and generous in our efforts to solve the race problem.
{DIALOGUE}: But we have to remember that the negro will bite if he gets the chance, just like a mongrel dog will bite if it crosses its mind to do so.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Is Coffey guilty?
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, he is.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you doubt it, and don't you turn your back on him.
{DIALOGUE}: You might get away with it once or even a hundred times...but in the end...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises his hand, making biting motions with his fingers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: You understand?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul says nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burt gazes out again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm gonna have to tear that old doghouse down one of these days.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PAUL'S MODEL T - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul drives back to Cold Mountain, his heart conflicted...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and he walks onto the Mile with a bundle wrapped in a dish towel.
