{DIALOGUE}: After, you take him down to Florida?
{DIALOGUE}: To dat Mouseville?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: We'll do it together, most likely.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe take a little vacation time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul moves to Coffey's cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mouse skitters off Paul's shoulder onto Coffey's hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: People pay a dime apiece to see him.
{DIALOGUE}: Two cents for the kiddies.
{DIALOGUE}: Ain't dat right, Boss Howell?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: That's right, Del.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: You a good man, Boss Howell.
{DIALOGUE}: You too, Boss Edgecomb.
{DIALOGUE}: Wish I could'a met you bot' someplace else.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del gives Mr. Jingles one last look, starts to cry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: Au revoir, mon ami.
{DIALOGUE}: Je t'aime, mon petit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And they start to walk the Mile...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: EXECUTION CHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sweltering in the damp heat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rain is pissing down, drumming the tin roof.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People glance up uneasily as THUNDER BOOMS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FAT LADY is staring grimly at the electric chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FAT LADY
{DIALOGUE}: Hope he's good and scared.
{DIALOGUE}: Hope he knows the fires are stoked, and that Satan's imps are waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON DOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del enters, horrified to see Percy waiting at Old Sparky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul gives Del's arm a reassuring squeeze, leads him forward...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN A TIGHT SERIES OF SHOTS:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The clamps are applied.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The straps are drawn tight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Roll on one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lights brighten on a RISING HUM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Witnesses look up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE MILE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey looks up as the overheads flare hotter and hotter, whispers to the mouse in his hands:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: You be still, Mr. Jingles.
{DIALOGUE}: You be so quiet and so still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME EXECUTION CHAMBER
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Eduard Delacroix, you have been condemned to die by a jury of your peers, sentence imposed by a judge in good standing in this state.
{DIALOGUE}: You have anything to say before sentence is carried out?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del tries to speak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doesn't quite manage the first time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Licks his lips and tries again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEL
{DIALOGUE}: I sorry for what I do.
{DIALOGUE}: I give anything to take it back, but I can't.
{DIALOGUE}: God have mercy on me.
{META_DATA}: (whispers to Paul)
{DIALOGUE}: Don' forget 'bout Mouseville.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and Brutal nod--and are stunned as:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: No such place.
{DIALOGUE}: That's just a fairy tale these guys told you to keep you quiet.
{DIALOGUE}: Just thought you should know, faggot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The stricken look in Del's eyes tells us a part of him had known all along.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and Brutal would both like to deck Percy right about now, and he knows it--he gives them a "what are you gonna do about it" smile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing they can do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul nods to Harry, who takes the black mask from the back of the chair and rolls it down over Del's head, leaving the top of his shaved head exposed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PERCY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: takes the sponge and bends down to the bucket of brine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other don't see it, but we do:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy only pretends to dip the sponge and soak it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It never touches the water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He straightens up and places the sponge atop Delacroix's head, hiding it with his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cap is lowered.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the others haven't yet realized what's happened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THUNDER BOOMS and LIGHTNING CRASHES as Percy hides a smile, steps back to address the condemned:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Electricity shall now be passed through your body until you are dead, in accordance with state law.
{DIALOGUE}: God have mercy on your soul.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON PAUL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as realization starts to dawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares at the bucket, then across the floor to Delacroix, coming to terms with the evidence of his eyes--there's no water on the floor or dripping down the sides of Del's neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul's eyes widen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A stunned beat of horror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts to open his mouth to scream "NO!"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: , but Percy beats him to it with:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Roll on two.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Van Hay flicks the switch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHAM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The electricity hits home and Del rocks forward, riding the current.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then things start to go horribly wrong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The HUMMING loses its steadiness and starts to waver with a CRACKLING SOUND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tendrils of smoke begin curling from under the cap, a mixture of burning hair and sponge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal shoots Paul a horrified look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul responds with a harsh whisper:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: It's dry!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Delacroix begins twisting and jittering in the chair, his masked face snapping violently from side to side, his legs pistoning up and down in his restraints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a MUFFLED POP from under the cap, like a pine knot exploding in a hot fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smoke starts coming through the fabric of the mask, puffing upward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del is being cooked alive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul spins to the partition, hollering--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: JACK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: --but Brutal grabs his arm, whispers fiercely:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you tell him to stop.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you do it.
{DIALOGUE}: It's too late for that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul turns back, helpless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other guards are trading wild looks, unable to believe what's happening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even Percy looks aghast--he was expecting something, but not this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del begins SCREAMING--the wild, hysterical sound of an animal being shredded alive in a hay baler.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The HUMMING goes uneven and ragged, the lights rising and falling...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE MILE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...as Del's screams rise and fall with them, echoing up the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's shaking and screaming too, as if feeling Del's pain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mr. Jingles squirms out of his grasp and goes squeaking in terror toward the restraint room door...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: HE'S COOKIN' NOW!
{DIALOGUE}: THEY COOKIN' HIM GOOD!
{DIALOGUE}: NEAR ABOUT DONE, I RECKON!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME EXECUTION CHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wrong.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del's nowhere near about done.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's slamming back and forth in the chair hard enough to shake the platform, twisting hard against the leather restraints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear BONES BREAKING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A WOMAN'S SCREAMS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Witnesses start rising to their feet:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WITNESSES
{DIALOGUE}: What the hell's happening to him?
{DIALOGUE}: ...Are those clamps going to hold?
{DIALOGUE}: ...Christ, the smell!
{DIALOGUE}: ...Is this normal?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mask bursts into flame on Delacroix's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Van Hay hollers through the wire mesh, horrified:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VAN HAY
{DIALOGUE}: SHOULD I KILL THE JUICE?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: NO!
{DIALOGUE}: ROLL, FOR CHRIST'S SAKE, ROLL!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry scoops up the bucket of water to throw it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No water!
{DIALOGUE}: No water!
{DIALOGUE}: You crazy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry backs off with a look of dazed understanding--you don't throw water on a man getting juiced.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops the bucket, races to get the chemical fire extinguisher instead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flaming mask peels away, revealing Del's charring face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyeballs are misshapen globs of burning white jelly blown out of their sockets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ATTENDING DOCTOR faints dead away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pandemonium now in the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People shouting and hurrying to exit, chairs falling over, women screaming:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FAT LADY
{DIALOGUE}: Stop it, stop it, oh can't you see he's had enough?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal grabs Paul by the shoulder, spins him around.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you shut it down?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: He's still alive!
{DIALOGUE}: You want me to shut down while he's still alive?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal is horrified at the thought.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del is jittering and screaming, rocking from side to side, smoke pouring from his nostrils and mouth, his tongue sizzling purple-black.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The witnesses are crowding and shoving to get out, but the back door is locked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All they can do is cluster there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul sees Percy with his head turned away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He grabs him, forces his head around.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: You watch, you son of a bitch!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry steps up, the extinguisher in his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Del finally slumps over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He still vibrating, but now it's just the effect of current flowing through his body.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Kill it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Van Hay kills the current.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The HUMMING DIES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal grabs the extinguisher from Harry, shoves it into Percy's hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: You do it.
{DIALOGUE}: You're running the show, ain't you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy, sick and dazed, aims the extinguisher and hoses the smoking corpse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal is near the back, calming the crowd:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: It's all right, folks, it's all under control.
{DIALOGUE}: Just a power surge from the storm, that's all, nothing to worry about...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Dean, get doc's stethoscope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean drops to the doctor's bag, digs through it, hands up the stethoscope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul plugs them into his ears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People are moaning and sobbing at the back of the room:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh my God!
{DIALOGUE}: Is it always like this?
{DIALOGUE}: Why didn't somebody tell me?
{DIALOGUE}: I never would have come!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul wipes some foam away from Delacroix's chest, places the stethoscope pad to the raw flesh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He nods to Brutal--it's over.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ACCESS TUNNEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the others bring the stretcher down, lay the corpse on the gurney.
