{DIALOGUE}: Let's not discuss this like it's even an option.
{DIALOGUE}: Brutal, help me out here...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal lets out a deep breath, considering.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks to Paul.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sure she's a fine woman...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: The finest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: What's happening to her is an offense, Brutal.
{DIALOGUE}: To the eyes and the ears and the heart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: I have no doubt.
{DIALOGUE}: But we don't know her like you and Jan do...do we?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: That's why it's a lot to ask.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: It is.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's not forget Coffey's a murderer.
{DIALOGUE}: What if he escapes?
{DIALOGUE}: I'd hate losing my job or going to prison, but I'd hate having a dead child on my conscience even more.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think that'll happen...
{META_DATA}: (beat, softly)
{DIALOGUE}: ...in fact, I don't think he did it at all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men are stunned by this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Off their looks:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I just can't see God putting a gift like that in the hands of a man who would kill a child.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, that's a tender notion, but the man's on death row for the crime.
{DIALOGUE}: Plus, he's huge.
{DIALOGUE}: If he tried to get away, it'd take a lot of bullets to stop him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: We'd all have shotguns in addition to sidearms.
{DIALOGUE}: I'd insist on that.
{META_DATA}: (to Paul)
{DIALOGUE}: He tried anything, we'd have to take him down.
{DIALOGUE}: You understand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I understand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: So.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell us what you had in mind.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN BLACKNESS, A TITLE CARD APPEARS:
{META_DATA}: "Night Journey"
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. INFIRMARY BUILDING/DISPENSARY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FLASHLIGHT BEAM plays across a glass cabinet, scanning the contents.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The beam pauses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A hand enters frame, unlocks the cabinet, pulls out a bottle of morphine tablets...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and WE ANGLE TO Brutal as he shakes half a dozen pills onto his palm, pockets them, replaces the bottle on the shelf.
