{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...while TOWER GUARDS huddle in their enclosure atop the walls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An occasional SPOTLIGHT cuts the darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIREFLIES dance in the fields and trees as far as the eye can see.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Four dark figures detach from the shadows, hurrying across the lonely country road into the fields on the far side...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WOODS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's hand scoops up some fallen leaves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TILT UP to his face as he crunches them under his nose, inhaling their smell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He see the guards throwing him anxious looks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He misreads this, holds out his hand so they can smell too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They do it, just to make him happy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: C'mon, big boy, keep moving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FEW FIREFLIES come winking through frame as the group presses on...
