{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry brings them to a thicket of trees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start removing branches and boughs, uncovering a battered old FARMALL TRUCK hidden in the brush.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even more fireflies are swirling around them, growing in number.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's getting downright weird.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey laughs softly, drawing their attention.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A childlike smile has utterly transformed his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises his hand, letting a firefly weave playfully in and out of his fingers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Hey there, little firefly.
