{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, there you is.
{DIALOGUE}: You come out to play too?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men stand gaping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fireflies are flitting to Coffey as if to a beacon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He waves his hands slowly, fireflies blinking and trailing from his fingertips like magic dust.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They begin orbiting his shiny bald head like tiny glowing planet orbiting a sun, their light kicking a mellow sheen off his ebony skin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's eyes meet Paul's.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: They seem...drawn to you.
