{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal's shotgun shifts back to Coffey--but Paul steps in front of the muzzle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No one's hurt.
{DIALOGUE}: We're here to help.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Help what?
{DIALOGUE}: I don't understand.
{DIALOGUE}: Is this a prison break?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I can't explain what it is.
{DIALOGUE}: You just have to trust me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey comes up the steps, brushes Paul aside, stops before the warden.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal blinks, his thoughts suddenly fuzzy--it's that benign hypnotic effect Coffey has.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: What do you...want?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Hal!
{DIALOGUE}: Make them go away!
{DIALOGUE}: No salesmen in the middle of the night!
{DIALOGUE}: No Fuller brushes!
{DIALOGUE}: No French knickers with come in the crotch!
{DIALOGUE}: Tell them to take a flying fuck in a rolling d..
{DIALOGUE}: d..
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the sound of GLASS BREAKING, then she begins to sob.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{META_DATA}: (a whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Just to help.
{DIALOGUE}: Just to help, boss, that's all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: You can't.
{DIALOGUE}: No one can.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey pulls the shotgun gently from Hal's grasp, hands it to Paul.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey moves past Hal into the house...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and comes up the hallway toward the stairs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you go up there!
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you do it!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Boss, you just be quiet now and let me be.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey mounts the stairs with the others at his heels, heading up toward that quavering voice:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Stay out of here!
{DIALOGUE}: Whoever you are, just stay out!
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not dressed for visitors, you rat's asshole!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey enters, trailed by the others.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul pauses, horrified.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The woman propped in bed barely resembles Melinda Moores anymore--she looks made up like a Halloween witch, her livid skin hanging in a loose trail of wrinkles, one corner of her mouth twisted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yellowish bile stains her chin and the front of her nightgown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hair has gone white and straw-like, her eyes glowering at Coffey with lively, irrational interest:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, so big!
{DIALOGUE}: Pull down your pants!
{DIALOGUE}: Let's have a look!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal groans with despair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey just stands there for a moment, watching her from a distance, then approaches the bed...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Don't come near me, pigfucker.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...but as he draws closer, a change occurs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her features soften, her eyes become more sane and aware.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you have so many scars?
{DIALOGUE}: Who hurt you so badly?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Don't hardly remember, ma'am.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey sits on the edge of the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lights seem to flare hotter and brighter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears are forming in Melinda's eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: What's your name?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: John Coffey, ma'am.
{DIALOGUE}: Like the drink, only not spelt the same.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She lays back, staring at him with shining fascination.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The world seems to be slowing down, growing very still indeed...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and he starts bending slowly toward her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Ma'am?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, John Coffey?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: I see it.
{DIALOGUE}: I see it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He comes closer...closer still...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: You be still now.
{DIALOGUE}: You be so quiet and so still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He brushes her forehead with his lips...the gentlest whisper of a kiss...then moves his mouth down to hers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: For a moment we can see one of her eyes staring past him, filling with an expression of surprise...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and then her face is lost to view as Coffey puts his lips on hers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear a soft whistling sound as he begins inhaling the air deeply from her lungs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something hot and glowing starts passing between them, drawn on his breath...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men watch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house seems to shudder in that moment, as if the entire world has shifted an inch to the right...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOWNSTAIRS PARLOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and the grandfather clock stops ticking, the pendulum stopping dead, the glass face cracking neatly up the center...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and a windowpane cracks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then another.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A picture falls off the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A lightbulb bursts, showering glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul smells smoke, realizes the fringed coverlet of the bed has caught fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moving like a man in a dream, he reaches for the waterglass on the nightstand, douses the flames.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey keeps kissing Melinda in that deep and mysterious way, inhaling and inhaling, her hand held in his like a tiny white bird.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: For a moment we actually hear something screaming, as if some willful imp were being extracted by force...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and then it's over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey raises his head, revealing:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Melinda's beautiful face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her mouth no longer droops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Color is coming back to her hair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her skin is shining with life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey regards her raptly for a moment or two, then starts coughing violently.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns away and drops to his knees, hacking like a man in the last stages of tuberculosis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and his men are expecting Coffey to spit out the "bugs", but he doesn't--he just keeps coughing, deep and hard, barely finding time to snatch in the next breath of air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal goes to his wife, beyond stunned, sits at her side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks back at him with amazement, her face like a dirty mirror that's been suddenly wiped clean.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John's coughing grows even worse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal drops to his side and slaps his broad, spasming back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: John!
{DIALOGUE}: Sick it up!
{DIALOGUE}: Cough 'em out like you done before!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey just keeps retching, eyes watering from the strain, spit flying from his mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: He's choking!
{DIALOGUE}: Whatever he sucked out of her, he's choking on it!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul starts toward them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey crawls away, pressing himself into a corner with his face against the wallpaper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's still making gruesome deep hacking sounds, but getting it under control.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He weakly waves Paul off--let me be.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul looks to the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal sits with Melinda, stroking her brow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Color is blooming in her cheeks even as we watch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: How did I get here?
{DIALOGUE}: We were going to the hospital in Indianola, weren't we?
{DIALOGUE}: We stopped and you bought me a packet of posies...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Shhh.
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't matter.
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't matter anymore.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Did I have the X-ray?
{DIALOGUE}: Did I
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They both look at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: It was clear.
{DIALOGUE}: There was no tumor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal bursts into tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Melinda sits up, comforting him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes are drawn to the corner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Who is that man?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey is struggling to rise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal does his best to help.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: John?
{DIALOGUE}: Can you turn around?
{DIALOGUE}: Can you turn around and see this lady?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face is ashen gray, seriously ill.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: What's your name?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: John Coffey, ma'am.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Like the drink, only not spelled the same.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: No, ma'am.
{DIALOGUE}: Not spelt the same at all.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pushes the covers aside to rise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal tries to stop her...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: Melly, no...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...but she pushes his hand gently aside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal watches in wonder as she stands, takes a first tentative step...and walks to Coffey.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She gazes up and touches his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: I dreamed of you.
{DIALOGUE}: I dreamed you were wandering in the dark, and so was I.
{DIALOGUE}: We found each other.
{DIALOGUE}: We found each other in the dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She undoes her necklace, holds it up for him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hesitates, glances to Paul.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul nods--it's all right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey lowers his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Melinda affixes the delicate chain around his neck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: It's St. Christopher.
{DIALOGUE}: I want you to have it, Mr. Coffey, and wear it.
{DIALOGUE}: He'll keep you safe.
{DIALOGUE}: Please wear it for me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, ma'am.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MELINDA
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you, John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her arms go around his neck, hugging him tightly as if she might never let go.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MOORES HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the men hustle Coffey out the front door toward the truck, helping him as best they can.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's weak as a baby, knees threatening to give out at any moment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: C'mon, John, stay on your feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: Christ, he goes down, we'll need three mules and a crane to pick him up again...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They get Coffey to the truck and throw their backs into it, helping him crawl up onto the stakebed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls over on his back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harry hops up, covers him with an old blanket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal pulls aside, speaking low:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: He'll never sit in Old Sparky.
{DIALOGUE}: You know that, don't you?
{META_DATA}: (off Paul's look)
{DIALOGUE}: He swallowed that stuff for a reason.
{DIALOGUE}: I give him a few days.
{DIALOGUE}: One of us'll be doing a cell check and there he'll be.
{DIALOGUE}: Dead on his bunk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: If that's his choice, he's earned it.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Let's get him back on the Mile.
{META_DATA}: FADE TO BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN BLACKNESS, A TITLE CARD APPEARS:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Coffey on the Mile"
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean starts babbling with relief as they return:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Am I glad to see you!
{DIALOGUE}: You were gone so long!
{DIALOGUE}: Wild Bill's making noises like he's gonna wake up...
{META_DATA}: (notices Coffey)
{DIALOGUE}: What the hell's wrong with him?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: He's hurting, Dean.
{DIALOGUE}: Hurting bad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean jumps in, helps them steer Coffey into his cell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: John, we're gonna set you on your bunk now.
{DIALOGUE}: Ready?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey nods, sits heavily on the bunk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lowers his head, breath rasping like a rusted hinge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guards step out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: What about Mrs. Moores?
