{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: Yes it was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul scans their faces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smiles are traded.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An exultant beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: Damn.
{DIALOGUE}: I think we got away with it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: We still gotta convince a certain somebody to keep his trap shut.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Get his stuff.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean hurries off to retrieve Percy's holster and baton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal unlocks the restraint room door, swings it open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy is revealed sitting against the wall, glaring, his mouth still taped.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul crouches down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal joins him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I want to talk, not shout.
{DIALOGUE}: I take the tape off, you gonna be calm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul takes hold of the tape, preparing to yank.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: My mother always said if you do it fast, it won't hurt so much.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul rips the tape off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy's eyes water with pain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: I guess she was wrong.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Get me out of this nut-coat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: In a minute.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Now!
{DIALOGUE}: Now!
{DIALOGUE}: Right n--
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul slaps him hard, knocks him sideways.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy looks up, blinking in surprise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul grabs him, yanks him back up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: You shut up and listen.
{DIALOGUE}: You deserved to be punished for what you did to Del.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll accept it like a man, or we'll make you sorry you were ever born.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll tell people how you sabotaged Del's execution--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: Sabotaged!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: --and how you pissed yourself like a frightened little girl.
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, we'll talk, that's a given--but, Percy, mind me now...we'll also see you beaten within an inch of your life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy blinks, unable to grasp that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: We know people, too, are you so foolish you don't realize that?
{DIALOGUE}: People with friends and loved ones doing time in this prison.
{DIALOGUE}: People who'd be happy to amputate you nose or your penis just so someone they care about could get an extra three hours in the exercise yard every week.
{META_DATA}: (off Percy's look)
{DIALOGUE}: Let bygones be bygones.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing's hurt so far but your pride...and nobody need ever know about that except the people in this room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: What happens on the Mile, stays on the Mile.
{DIALOGUE}: Always has.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PERCY
{DIALOGUE}: May I be let out of this coat now?
