{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy exits the restraint room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal whispers to Paul:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: He'll talk.
{DIALOGUE}: Sooner or later.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul nods with weary resignation--yeah, I know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE MILE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy pauses near Coffey's cell, careless as always, getting his holster buckled--and a massive black arm grabs him through the bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His SCREAM brings Paul and the others from the restraint room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey's face is pressed so tight between his bars it looks like he's trying to push his head through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He draws his lips back, baring his teeth in an awful sneer...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy whacks him with his baton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey barely seems to feel it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He curls his free hand around the back of Percy's head, pulling him ever closer...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and Percy's screams are muffled as their mouths come together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey begins exhaling as if he'd held his breath for hours.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy jerks like a fish on a hook, but can't get away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men jump in, try to pry Percy loose, hollering for Coffey to let him go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The black "insects" are flowing from Coffey to Percy, swirling into his mouth, up his nose, down his throat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several lightbulbs explode in their steel cages up and down the Mile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy's baton drops from his nerveless fingers and clatters to the floor, never to be picked up again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And then Coffey steps back, rubbing his mouth as if he's tasted something bad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The color has returned to his skin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy, however, is ashen gray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His expression is blank as a sheet of paper, not a trace of awareness in his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men are stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul raises his hand to Percy's face, snaps his fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries again, clapping loudly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy reacts slightly, eyes fluttering, swaying a bit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Easy, easy.
{DIALOGUE}: You all right?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy says nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and walks slowly up the Mile, his movements vacant and disjointed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He comes to a swaying stop at Wild Bill's cell...and turns slowly to look in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wild Bill is coming painfully around, groggily clutching his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up, see Percy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: What'a you looking at, you limp noodle?
{DIALOGUE}: You wanna kiss my ass or suck my dick?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing for the longest moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy just staring...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and then he pulls his gun and empties it into Wild Bill as fast as he can pull the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BAM!BAM!BAM!BAM!BAM!BAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bill takes all six rounds in the chest, reeling back across the cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hits the wall and slides down, leaving a smear, his face registering a final look of stunned surprise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the other tackle Percy and bring him down, wrestling the gun out of his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean is almost weeping:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh God, oh God, no...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Percy is flat on his back, staring up at nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The black "bugs" come drifting out of nose and mouth, swirling in the air over his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They turn white and disappear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men are speechless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul turns, sees Coffey sitting on the floor at his bars, watching.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Punished them bad men.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Why Wild Bill?
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: I saw in his heart.
{DIALOGUE}: When he grab my arm, I saw what Wild Billy done.
{DIALOGUE}: Saw plain as day.
{DIALOGUE}: Can't hide what's in your heart.
