{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and Paul sees:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Detterick twins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kathe and Cora.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Laughing and playing hopscotch in the dust under a later afternoon sun...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A dinner table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Family having supper late in the day, basket of biscuits being passed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Twelve year old Howie Detterick taking it, passing it on...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An hand with a paint brush slopping bright red paint on the side of a barn...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kathe skipping to the head of the hopscotch squares, turning and starting back, laughing in the sun...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The paint brush slopping more paint, dripping like blood...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul jerks and twists, trying to pull away, trying to break the circuit, but he can't, not till all is seen and done:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Marjorie Detterick calling from the porch for everybody to come eat, supper's ready...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A hammer pausing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Klaus looking down from atop the barn...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Detterick twins finishing their hopscotch, gathering their jump ropes from the dust, running across the yard...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The basket of biscuits being passed to little Cora, who takes a biscuit and passes it on...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Klaus coming down the ladder, calling to his daughters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The little girls running past the man with the paint brush, who turns and smile as they go by...it's Wild Bill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The basket of biscuits is passed one last time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A hand pulls one out, raises it for a bite.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's Wild Bill, smiling at the little girls as conversation flows around the table...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul screams, trying to pull away, but:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The porch door is kicked off its hinges just before dawn, a figure looming in the doorway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kathe wakes, her scream cut short as the man's fist punches her hard in the face...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul trembles violently as if riding the lightning himself, pleading for it to stop, but there's one last thing:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wild Bill looms over the terrified little girls like a horrendous boogeyman, whispers to Kathe:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: You lover your sister?
{DIALOGUE}: You make any noise, know what happens?
{DIALOGUE}: I'll kill her instead of you.
{META_DATA}: (to Cora)
{DIALOGUE}: And if you make any noise, I'll kill her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And he drags them out into the coming dawn...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...as Coffey lets Paul go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is gasping, back in the real world where his men are staring at him with wide eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: He kill 'em with they love.
{DIALOGUE}: They love for each other.
{DIALOGUE}: You see how it is?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul nods, numb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears are flowing down Coffey's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: That's how it is ever' day.
{DIALOGUE}: That's how it is all over the worl'...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WILD BILL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: lies dead, staring with glassy eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FLASHBULB POPS, rimming him with harsh blue light...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - DAWN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...as Hal arrives, wearing his pajama top under his overcoat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the POLICE PHOTOGRAPHER taking pictures.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guards are giving statements to GROUPS OF COPS, everybody murmuring:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: ...well, I dunno, he just snapped, I guess...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: ...s'right, one minute he's fine, the next--blammo...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: ...bastard grabbed him through the bars a few days back, scared the boy so bad he wet himself...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hal turns, sees:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PERCY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sits handcuffed on the floor of the Mile, eyes glassier than Wild Bill's.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO COPS are trying to snap him out of it:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COP #1
{DIALOGUE}: Son!
{DIALOGUE}: Son!
{DIALOGUE}: Can you hear me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COP #2
{DIALOGUE}: Speak up if you can hear us!
{DIALOGUE}: We gotta ask you some questions!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MEDIC is raising Percy's eyelid with his thumb, shining a penlight, getting no reaction.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MEDIC
{DIALOGUE}: I think this boy's cheese slid off his cracker.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HAL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sees Paul, motions him aside to talk privately:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAL
{DIALOGUE}: I'll cover you as much as I can, even if it mean my job, but I have to know.
{DIALOGUE}: Does this have anything to do with what happened at my house?
{DIALOGUE}: Does it, Paul?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul looks Hal in the eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As with Bitterbuck, the lie comes easy:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOSPITAL ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TRACKING A PAIR OF FEET shuffling into the room in hospital slippers, escorted by TWO ORDERLIES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The patient is brought to a window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderlies turn to leave...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and we BOOM UP to reveal Percy, catatonic, staring out the same window where we met Wild Bill...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOSPITAL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ...and we WIDEN SLOWLY from Percy at the window to reveal his last stop in life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's emblazoned on the gate: BRIAR RIDGE MENTAL HOSPITAL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He finally got that transfer.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PAUL'S HOUSE - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON PAUL as softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: It makes sense.
{DIALOGUE}: I read the file.
{DIALOGUE}: Hal even said it himself.
{DIALOGUE}: Wharton rambled all over the state last few years, causing trouble.
{DIALOGUE}: Hell, longer than that.
{DIALOGUE}: Been at it since he was ten.
{DIALOGUE}: Vandalism.
{DIALOGUE}: Petty theft.
{DIALOGUE}: Setting fires.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE SHIFTS to include Jan, Brutal, Harry and Dean.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're in the brambly patch that borders the woods behind the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sun is setting, turning the horizon fiery.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: You saw him.
{DIALOGUE}: You actually saw this Wild Bill person take those girls.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Their father hired him on for a few days last spring, help repair the barn.
{DIALOGUE}: Cheap labor, just another drifter...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Only not.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Sick bastard came back a month later, just before dawn.
{DIALOGUE}: Took the girls...did what he did.
{DIALOGUE}: Coffey found them afterwards and tried to help.
{DIALOGUE}: It was too late.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{META_DATA}: (absorbs this)
{DIALOGUE}: Then you can stop it.
{DIALOGUE}: The execution, I mean.
{DIALOGUE}: Get Coffey a new trial.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Based on what, honey?
{DIALOGUE}: Some kind of magical vision I had?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Show this farmer--what's his name, Detterick?
{DIALOGUE}: --show him a picture of Wild Bill.
{META_DATA}: (off their looks)
{DIALOGUE}: Why not?
{DIALOGUE}: If Wharton was there...if the farmer can identify his picture and they know he was there...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Him being there in May doesn't mean he came back and killed those girls in June.
{DIALOGUE}: Even if he was committing other crimes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: They got their killer as far as they're concerned.
{DIALOGUE}: Hell, Coffey's own lawyer would come throw the switch if we let him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Then lie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Lie?
{DIALOGUE}: About what?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Tell them Wharton confessed to the crime.
{DIALOGUE}: Brutus, you can back him up, say you heard it too.
{DIALOGUE}: You can say that's what set Percy off.
{DIALOGUE}: He shot Wharton because he couldn't stand thinking of what happened to those two little girls, it snapped his mind...
{META_DATA}: (seeing their looks)
{DIALOGUE}: ...what?
{DIALOGUE}: What now?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: We never reported anything like that.
{DIALOGUE}: We would've, too, everybody knows it.
{DIALOGUE}: It's part of our job.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Besides, confessing don't make it so.
{DIALOGUE}: Slugs like Wild Bill lie about everything.
{DIALOGUE}: Crimes they committed, women they had, even the weather.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: But he was there!
{DIALOGUE}: He painted their barn!
{DIALOGUE}: He ate dinner with them!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: All the more reason he might take credit for the crime.
{DIALOGUE}: He's gonna fry anyway, so why not boast?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan stands thinking for a moment, then:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: All right.
{DIALOGUE}: Then you've got to get John Coffey out on your own.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: Ma'am?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: You did it once, didn't you?
{DIALOGUE}: Only this time, don't bring him back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dean blinks, stunned by this notion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gently:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Ma'am, your son's grown up and moved away.
{DIALOGUE}: My kids are just starting kindergarten.
{DIALOGUE}: Will you be the one to explain to them why their daddy's in prison?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Work out a plan.
{DIALOGUE}: Make it look like a real escape.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRY
{DIALOGUE}: Better be a plan an imbecile could dream up.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody'd believe it otherwise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: Even if we did think of something, it wouldn't do any good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Why not?
{DIALOGUE}: Just why the hell not?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Because he's a six-foot-eight-inch baldheaded black man with barely enough brains to feed himself.
{DIALOGUE}: How long you think it'd be before he was recaptured?
{DIALOGUE}: Two hours?
{DIALOGUE}: Six?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan swipes a tear away with the heel of her hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Do you mean to kill him, you cowards?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul tries to take her hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She wrenches away, furious.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Don't touch me!
{DIALOGUE}: Next week this time you'll be a murderer, no better than that man Wharton, so don't touch me!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She runs off toward the house, starting to sob as we
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INT PAUL'S KITCHEN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul is at the kitchen table in the wee hours, at his regular place, sipping his beer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Irving Berlin's "Remember" PLAYS SOFTLY on the radio.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jan comes down, looking miserable and exhausted.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm so sorry I called you a coward.
{DIALOGUE}: I feel worse about that than anything I've ever said to you in our whole marriage.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Even that time we went camping and you called me Old Stinky Sam?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She can't help smiling at that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He returns the smile, offers her a sip of beer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes it, sits.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Does Hal know?
{DIALOGUE}: That Coffey's innocent, I mean?
{META_DATA}: (Paul shakes his head)
{DIALOGUE}: Can he help?
{DIALOGUE}: Does he have the influence to do something about this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Then don't tell him.
{DIALOGUE}: If he can't help, don't tell him.
{DIALOGUE}: Ever.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I won't.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: There's no way out of this for you, is there?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: I've been thinking about it, too, believe me.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Tell you the truth, honey.
{DIALOGUE}: I've done some things in my life I'm not proud of, but this is the first time I've ever felt in real danger of hell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAN
{DIALOGUE}: Hell?
{DIALOGUE}: Oh Paul...
{META_DATA}: (touches his face)
{DIALOGUE}: Talk to him.
{DIALOGUE}: Talk to John.
{DIALOGUE}: Find out what he wants.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. E BLOCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey sits quietly in his cell, a solitary firefly flitting in circles around his finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the men appear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The firefly flits away, vanishing through Coffey's tiny window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, boss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brutal unlocks his cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul enters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I guess you know we're coming down to it now.
{DIALOGUE}: Another couple of days.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Is there anything special you'd like for dinner that night?
{DIALOGUE}: We can rustle you up most anything.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey gives it some careful thought.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Meatloaf be nice.
{DIALOGUE}: Mashed taters with gravy.
{DIALOGUE}: Okra, maybe.
{DIALOGUE}: I's not picky.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: What about a preacher?
{DIALOGUE}: Someone you could say a little prayer with?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Don't want no preacher.
{DIALOGUE}: You can say a prayer, if you want.
{DIALOGUE}: I could get kneebound with you, I guess.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey gives him a look--please.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: S'pose I could, if it came to that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul sits, working himself up to it:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: John, I have to ask you something very important right now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: I know what you gonna say.
{DIALOGUE}: You don' have to say it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: I do.
{DIALOGUE}: I do have to.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: John, tell me what you want me to do.
{DIALOGUE}: You want me to take you out of here?
{DIALOGUE}: Just let you run away?
{DIALOGUE}: See how far you can get?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: Why would you do such a foolish thing?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul hesitates, emotions swirling, trying to find the right words.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: On the day of my judgement, when I stand before God, and He asks me why did I kill one of his true miracles, what am I gonna say?
{DIALOGUE}: That is was my job?
{DIALOGUE}: My job?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: You tell God the Father it was a kindness you done.
{META_DATA}: (takes his hand)
{DIALOGUE}: I know you hurtin' and worryin', I can feel it on you, but you oughtta quit on it now.
{DIALOGUE}: Because I want it over and done.
{DIALOGUE}: I do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey hesitates--now he's the one trying to find the right words, trying to make Paul understand:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tired, boss.
{DIALOGUE}: Tired of bein' on the road, lonely as a sparrow in the rain.
{DIALOGUE}: Tired of not ever having me a buddy to be with, or tell me where we's coming from or going to, or why.
{DIALOGUE}: Mostly I'm tired of people being ugly to each other.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm tired of all the pain I feel and hear in the world ever' day.
{DIALOGUE}: There's too much of it.
{DIALOGUE}: It's like pieces of glass in my head all the time.
{DIALOGUE}: Can you understand?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: By now, Paul is blinking back tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PAUL
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, John.
{DIALOGUE}: I think I can.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BRUTAL
{DIALOGUE}: There must be something we can do for you, John.
{DIALOGUE}: There must be something you want.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Coffey thinks about this long and hard, finally looks up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
{DIALOGUE}: I ain't never seen me a flicker show.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON COFFEY'S FACE
