{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRED ASTAIRE
{META_DATA}: (singing)
{DIALOGUE}: Heaven, I'm in heaven...and my heart beats so that I can hardly speak...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paul and the men are scattered about in the otherwise empty auditorium, also watching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PROJECTION BOOTH
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toot operates the projector, peering through the tiny window into the theater.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He yawns, glances at his watch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Late.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE AUDITORIUM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fred and Ginger are now in the most passionate and graceful part of the dance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Irving Berlin's music swells.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COFFEY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: can't believe what he's seeing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's so excited his breath is caught in his throat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Softly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COFFEY
